Sure, here are five example sentences in Serbian that use the word "udariti" in different forms and positions. I will mark the word with a star (*) and provide an English translation in parenthesis.

1. *Udarila* je pesnicom u sto kada je saznala vest. (She *hit* the table with her fist when she heard the news.)
2. Moramo *udariti* temelje pre nego što počnemo gradnju kuće. (We need to *lay* the foundations before we start building the house.)
3. Sinoć sam *udario* glavom o ivicu kreveta i osetio jak bol. (Last night, I *hit* my head on the edge of the bed and felt a strong pain.)
4. Da bi dobili dobar zvuk, treba *udariti* po bubnju jače. (To get a good sound, you need to *hit* the drum harder.)
5. Policajac je *udario* rukom o sto i rekao nam da sednemo. (The police officer *slapped* his hand on the table and told us to sit down.)

I hope these examples are helpful!